    - target: {fileID: 2159534897854115432, guid: 2a2ce11149770fe4fa922461123a0821, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "A vaccine for the respiratory disease, NRD-99, that has been spreading
        across the country, has been finished testing and is starting to be rolled-out.
        The government is setting up vaccination sites in various areas. \r\nHere\u2019s
        what you need to know:\r\n\r\n1. The vaccine lowers chances of being infected,
        but doesn\u2019t completely prevent it.\r\n2. The vaccine has a side effect
        of being feverish for around 3 days after vaccination. This is the result
        of your body learning to fight against the disease.\r\n"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
